fields.biography:
Greta is a high school junior from Canada. She has qualified
              for USAJMO twice and attended MOP in 2024. She loves interacting
              with the math community; she hopes to share her passion for math
              and inspire other girls to enjoy the subject as well. Outside of
              math, Greta enjoys chess and listening to music.

Greta will be teaching *Combo Heuristics* this Fall!
              She also taught *Combo Heuristics* during the 2024-2025 school year!

Greta was also an Athemath student from 2022 to 2024!

Catherine is a high school senior at West High School in Iowa
              City, IA. She began doing math competitions seriously in 2020,
              beginning with her junior high’s math team. She attended MOP in
              2024 and placed 6th and 5th at Math Prize for Girls in 2022 and
              2023. Outside of math, Catherine can be found listening to music
              and taking walks outside!

Catherine will be teaching *Fun + Heights* this Fall!
            She also taught *Fun + Heights* during the 2024-2025 school year!

As Community Director, Catherine will manage Athemath community events to help students
              and staff connect outside of class settings!

Catherine was also an Athemath student in 2021 and 2022!

Rachel is a senior residing in California but originally from Canada. She's qualified for USAJMO, 
              CMO, and APMO and the Canada IMO Training Camp. Outside of olympiad math, she enjoys studying higher 
              math: she attended Canada/USA Mathcamp in 2023 and is a participant in the PRIMES-USA program. You 
              can often find her studying higher math, especially algebraic combinatorics. She also enjoys chess, 
              having participated in numerous international tournaments. Outside of math and chess, she enjoys 
              reading (her favorite author is Ishiguro), writing, Taylor Swift, and talking on discord.

As Contests Director, Rachel will coordinate Athemath team participation at various contests, including
              HMMT, PUMaC, CMIMC, and CMM.

Patrick from Thailand, also known as Celestia in some communities,
              is a current MIT student in the Class of 2029. He went to MOP 2023
              as an international student (black group), and also got a gold in
              IMO 2023 scoring at 35/42. He is a combi main first and foremost,
              but geo appeals to him as well. He does rhythm games but is not
              that good at them (rn it’s just arcaea), and he also enjoys being
              an MO trainer for some of his friends during his free time.
              Outside maths, he also aspires to be a researcher in computational
              neuroscience someday. He is so so excited to meet with all of
              you!!!

As Math Director, Patrick will ensure quality of the math
              curriculum and class materials.

Vera is in her fifth year at NUS High School
              (equivalent to high school junior) in Singapore, and has qualified
              for SIMO Senior Team in 2023 and 2024, and won a silver medal at
              the CGMO in 2024. She hopes to foster the interests of other girls
              in mathematics. She also enjoys physics olympiads and tournaments,
              as well as ballet and music.

As International Outreach Director, Vera will help spread the word
              about Athemath to communities around the globe!

Vivian (v4913) is a current Caltech student in the Class of 2028, 
              originally from Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. She loves math, especially geometry, and
              she attended MOP in 2021-2023 and was part of the U.S. team at the
              EGMO in 2022 and 2023. Aside from doing cool math problems, she
              also enjoys listening to EDM, origami, biking, teaching, and
              interacting with the math community.

Vivian taught *Cute Geometry* in Fall 2021, Spring 2022, Fall 2022,
              Spring 2023, Fall 2024, and Spring 2025, and *NT Olympiad Fundamentals*
              in Fall 2023 and Spring 2024!

Vivian was the President of Athemath from 2023 to 2024 and Community Director from 2022 to 2023!

Ali is a senior at MIT. She was an Honorable Mention for the 2020
              USAJMO, and was on the 2020 USA European Girls' Math Olympiad
              team, at which she got a silver medal. She started doing math
              contests seriously in seventh grade. While participating in math
              contests, she saw the way in which girls were isolated in math and
              how that helped lead to the under-representation of girls at
              contests. She founded Athemath in 2020 in order to help math girls
              connect to each other. Nowadays, Ali enjoys programming and
              reading webcomics.

Evan Chen (v_Enhance) completed his math PhD at
              MIT and is one of the coaches of the USA IMO team. As a high school
              student, Evan was an IMO gold medalist and winner of the 2014
              USAMO (which he took from 12:30am to 5am in Taiwan). Outside of
              math and teaching, Evan enjoys playing competitive Hanabi and
              entertaining students on Twitch.

Amy is a high school senior at Lakeside School in Washington. She
              has qualified for USAJMO three times and attended MOP in 2023 and
              2024. Her love for math began in elementary school, and she is
              excited to share this passion with other young girls. Outside of
              math, she enjoys fencing, running, reading, and listening to
              music.

Amy will be teaching *Outstanding Olympiad Geometry* this Fall! She also taught 
              *Outstanding Olympiad Geometry* during the 2023-2024 and 2024-2025 school years!

Ekam is a senior at Stanford Online High School. She has been
              doing math contests since elementary and attended MOP in 2023 and 2025. Her
              favorite math subject is combinatorics. Outside of math, she likes
              reading, digital art, and listening to music.

Ekam will be teaching *Classy Adventures in Combinatorics and Algebra*
              this Fall! She also taught *Classy Adventures in Combinatorics and Algebra* during 
              the 2024-2025 school year!

Jiya is a high school senior at the Liberal Arts and Science
              Academy in Austin, TX. They started their journey of learning
              competition math in the middle of 7th grade, and since then have
              qualified for USAJMO twice, attended MOP in 2024, and are a
              participant of the PRIMES-USA math research program. Outside of
              math, Jiya enjoys playing guitar, learning electronics, and
              chilling to ambient guitar music or vibing to random pop music.

Jiya will be teaching *NT Terrain Navigation* this Fall! They also taught
             *NT Terrain Navigation* during the 2024-2025 school year!

Lanie is a sophomore at Central High School in Springfield, Missouri. 
              She attended MOP in 2025, and her favorite olympiad subject is combinatorics. 
              Outside of math, Lanie enjoys playing card/board games, crocheting, doing puzzles, 
              occasionally playing the piano, and sculpting random things!

Lanie will be teaching *AIME Geo* this Fall!

Lanie was also an Athemath student from 2023 to 2025!

Pimmy from Thailand is a postgraduate student at the Hotchkiss School in Connecticut.
              She attended MOP 2023 as an international student and she is in TST
              camp in her country. Apart of Math, Pimmy likes taking a walk,
              reading webtoon and she also like a ton of other stuffs too.

Pimmy will be teaching *Get to Know Number Theory* this Spring! She also taught 
              *Get to Know Number Theory* during the 2023-2024 and 2024-2025 school years!

Selena is a sophomore at Lexington High School in Massachusetts. 
              She has competed in math competitions since elementary school and attended MOP in 2025. 
              Other than math, she enjoys reading, cryptograms, and sudokus.

Selena will be teaching *Cute Geometry* this Fall!

Selena was also an Athemath student from 2022 to 2023!

Sophia is a high school senior at Stuyvesant High School in New
              York City. She attended MOP in 2024. Her favorite olympiad subject
              is geometry, and outside of math, Sophia enjoys drawing, singing,
              listening to music, and hanging out with friends.

Sophia will be teaching *Nifty NT and Algebra* this Fall! She also taught 
              *Nifty NT and Algebra* during the 2024-2025 school year!

Wendy is a Y4 (10th grade) student from Raffles Girls' School,
              Singapore. She attended MOP 2023, 2024, and 2025 as an international student, and
              is a member of the SIMO National Team 2024. She is fascinated by
              the creativity and depth behind math problems, and is eager to
              share this passion with likeminded young girls!

Besides math, she also likes Kakuro, Killer Sudoku, and painting
              digitally on Procreate.

Wendy will be teaching *ComboneNT* this Fall! She also taught *ComboneNT* 
              during the 2024-2025 school year!

Akshitaa Arun (Akshu/Ash) is from Tamil Nadu, India. She has attended various math camps
              in India such as PROMYS INDIA 2024, RAMTP 2023, AGMNC 2022 & 2023. She's part of the outreach team
              in the Urban Harmony Project and ParagonX. She co-runs the math philosophy program NC^2.
              She enjoys tutoring her friends outside school, and showing them that math can be fun!
              Outside of math, she loves singing, playing the ukulele, playing card games or puzzles(especially killer sudoku),
              waveboarding and reading!

Arjun is a sophomore at Middleton High School in Wisconsin.
              He is a two-time AIME qualifier and received honors on USAJMO in 2025.
              Apart from math, he enjoys listening to music, reading, and writing.

Dóra is a senior high school student from Hungary and a member of the 2025 MEMO team.
              She attended MOP 2025 and has participated in different math camps and European competitions.
              Her favorite Olympiad subjects are combinatorics and geometry. Outside of math, Dóra enjoys
              doing sports like handball, reading, and listening to music.

Heather is a junior at the Harker School in California. 
              She attended MOP in 2025, and her favorite subjects are combinatorics and geometry.
              Outside of math, she likes to read, play the piano, and listen to music.

Jingni, from Australia, is a sophomore at the University of Sydney. He is an Australia MO 2024 Gold Medalist, 
              and has qualified for Australia TSTs in 2023 and 2024. His favourite math genre is combinatorics, 
              but his general math interest lies in uncovering the problem-solving process itself. 
              Outside of math, he enjoys playing chess, squash, photography, journaling and music composition.

Jingni ran the *Cherry Seminar Series* during the Spring 2025 session!

Lillian is a senior at Shanghai World Foreign Language Academy. She has participated in a 
              number of math competitions like AMC 12 and AIME, qualifying for USAMO, as well as team 
              competitions like BMT. She was also a student in the Ross Mathematics Program in Summer 2024. 
              Other than math, she enjoys playing frisbee and boxing, and is also a huge fan of musicals. 
              She is also the president of the Gender Studies club at her school.

This is Paras from India! He loves Maths(A=N>>>C>>>>>>G) and football (Madridista) and other 
              sports as well. When he is not doing Maths he tries to explore new places, food, and other stuffs! 
              He is always down to interacting with new people.

Ritwin is a current Stanford student in the Class of 2029. He began doing math competitions
              in elementary school, and his passion was ignited in high school after
              being introduced to the online math community. Ritwin attended MOP in 2024
              and USACO Camp in 2023. Besides math, he loves playing card games and
              chatting with people, as well as red pandas and the blobheart
              emoji (so wholesome :D).

He also runs the Problem of the Day seasons in Athemath and is
              excited to show cool problems to all of you!

Swastika is from Kolkata. She has been doing competition math for
              3 years and has taken part in various competitions. Her favorite
              subjects are geometry and number theory. She is a Sophie fellow
              and a staff at MOTP. Apart from math, she loves listening to
              Taylor Swift songs and playing the guitar.

Tarun is a junior from Houston, Texas. He is a 2025 USAMO Silver Medalist and a MOP attendee. 
              He is also part of the MIT PRIMES-USA research program and has attended Canada/USA Mathcamp in 
              2024 and 2025. In his free time, Tarun enjoys solving Olympiad Geometry problems, playing PC 
              games, and hanging out with friends.

Uddipa, a senior from Kolkata, India, loves Maths (specially combi and NT :)) and Physics. 
              She has excelled in IOQM, RMO, MO (IITB), BMT, the Sir Isaac Newton Exam (UoWaterloo), 
              TOSC (IITK), FSJM, IRO, and other contests. She has attended MTRP (ISI K), Math.Biz (RAM), 
              IISF (Govt. of India), Perimeter Institute, and SAIFR Brazil programs. A trained Odissi 
              dancer who enjoys editing, Uddipa is Vice President of the Math Club at Entwinity. She also 
              loves teaching maths and is passionate about making STEM opportunities more accessible, 
              especially for girls.

Emily is a current MIT student in the Class of 2029.
              She has done math competitions since elementary school, has
              attended MOP in 2023 and 2024, and also placed 5th at the 2022
              Math Prize for Girls competition. Outside of math, she enjoys card
              games, pole-vaulting, and drawing.

Emily taught *Adorable Algebra* during the 2023-2024 school year!

Emily was Community Director during the 2024-2025 school year!

Andrew is a current MIT student in the Class of 2029. An avid
              fan of math olympiads, he attended MOP in 2023. His favorite
              subject is combinatorics, which he hopes to understand more
              advanced theory in. Outside of math, Andrew enjoys playing the
              piano, running long distances, reading contemporary poetry, and
              listening to R&B.

Andrew was Contests Director during the 2024-2025 school year!

Neal is a math contest enthusiast from the Bay Area, despite
              growing up in Wisconsin, and Athemath TA since F23.
              Although mostly retired from the olympiad math world after MOP
              2023, he spends much of his time on making problem proposals by
              messing around on GeoGebra. Other than that, he also does random
              things like listening to a random classical / electronic music,
              making philosophical blog posts on AoPS, and making geometry
              diagrams with asy.

Matilde Iannaccone is a student at the University of Pisa and Scuola Normale Superiore in Italy.
              She attended MOP in 2023 as an international
              student and attended TST camps in her country. Her favorite
              subject in Math is Geometry but she is slowly starting to
              appreciate Combinatorics. Apart from Math she enjoys reading comic
              books, listening to Harry Styles and hanging out with friends.

Matilde taught *AIME Combo* during the 2023-2024 and 2024-2025 school years!

Julia Xiang is a current MIT student in the Class of 2029. She has been
              participating in math contests for several years and attended MOP
              in 2024. Her favorite subject is number theory, but over the years
              she has come to love all math for its fun and challenges. Outside
              of math, Julia likes writing and listening to music.

Julia taught *Affable Algebraic Affairs* during the 2024-2025 school year!

Emily is a current MIT student in the Class of 2029.
              She has been doing math competitions since elementary and middle
              school and she attended MOP in 2023. She especially enjoys
              olympiad geometry. Outside of math, Emily likes to go on hikes
              with her family, hanging out with friends, and listening to music.

Emily taught *Comical Combo* during the 2023-2024 and 2024-2025 school years!

Ashley Zhu is a current Harvard student in the Class of 2029. 
              She attended MOP ‘23. She hopes to help girls feel more
              comfortable pursuing math. Outside of math, she loves to read,
              draw, and write.

Ashley taught
              *Art of Trigonometry (ft. Problem Solving)* during the 2023-2024 and 2024-2025 school years!

Ana is a current Princeton student in the Class of 2029. 
              She is an EGMO 2023 gold medalist and she attended MOP in 2023 as an international
              student. Her favourite part of Math is Geometry, but she can get
              along with Number Theory if need be. Outside of Math, she enjoys
              writing (about anything), playing table tennis and going on long
              walks.

Ana taught *Quirky Geometry* during the 2023-2024 and 2024-2025 school years!

Peyton is a current MIT student in the Class of 2029. Ever since starting math competitions in
              elementary school, Peyton has participated in the Canadian Winter
              Training Camp and MOP in 2022 and 2023 respectively. His favorite
              subject is combinatorics, but he used to be much better at
              geometry. When not doing math, you can find Peyton playing
              quizbowl, piano, or reading random wikipedia articles.

Laura is currently a year 12 in Australia, having attended the EGMO
              twice and the IMO once and obtaining a gold medal each time.

When she's not chatting with other maths enthusiasts, she enjoys
              badminton, listening to music, losing the game, making the
              smallest origami cranes humanly possible and playing board/card
              games.

A math enthusiast from India, Yash was a part of the training camp
              for the IMO team in 2024.He has participated in various math
              contests throughout his high school years and especially likes
              combinatorics even though he is an NT main. When not doing math,
              he likes to swim, hangout with friends and spend numerous hours on
              his phone.

Alexander is a current student at Millburn High School graduating in 2026.
              He is a 2-time IMO Gold Medalist in 2023 and 2024.
              He won a gold medal at RMM 2023 and APMO 2024.
              He is a 2-time USAMO Gold Medalist and obtained a perfect score in 2023.
              He attended the prestigious MOP program from 2022-2024.
              He attended the MIT PRIMES-USA math research program in 2024.
              In his spare time, he enjoys playing sports, especially tennis.

Angeline is a current Harvard student in the Class of 2029. She
              qualified for the USAJMO and received several awards for females
              in mathematics, including the Maryam Mirazkhani award. She loves
              sharing her passion for math with other students. Outside of math,
              Angeline loves journalism and playing poker with her friends.

Hannah is a current MIT student in the Class of 2029. She attended MOP
              in 2023 and 2024, and G2 in 2023. She was also an Athemath student
              in the spring 2022 session.

Hannah taught *AIME Geo* in Fall 2023 and Spring 2024!

Sunaina is a third year student at CMI. She is an EGMO 2023
              silver medalist and attended IMO training Camp three times. In her
              free time, she loves to write blogposts, work on some Olympiad
              math problems and talk to her friends. She also loves to watch
              romcom k-dramas and listen to k-pop and Indian Indies.

Serena is a current MIT student in the Class of 2026 majoring in math. In high school, she
              was a two-time MOP qualifier and EGMO gold medalist, and before
              college, she took a gap year to study abroad in South Korea. She
              also founded the Brookings Math Circle and ran it for five years
              to address the lack of math interest and resources in her town. In
              her free time, she enjoys playing card games, learning languages,
              and going on walks.

Serena taught *Computational Geometry* in Spring 2021!

Michelle Kang is a current MIT student in the Class of 2028 who attended Thomas Jefferson
              High School for Science and Technology in Virginia. She attended
              MOP in 2021 and 2022 and has competed in math contests from a
              young age. She hopes to inspire and motivate other girls who have
              a passion in STEM. Outside of math, she loves watching movies,
              playing card games (especially ERS), and playing table tennis.

Michelle taught *Counting Strategies* in Fall 2021, Spring
              2022, Fall 2022, and Spring 2023!

Michelle was Community Director during the 2023-2024 school year!

Laura Zhang is a current MIT student in the Class of 2028 who attended Thomas Jefferson
              High School for Science and Technology in northern Virginia. She
              attended MOP in 2022 and also competes with her school's math
              team. Laura hopes to encourage young girls and nonbinary people to
              continue pursuing their dreams. Along with math, she enjoys
              journalism, reading romance novels, and having meaningful
              conversations.

Laura taught *Algebra and NT Fundamentals* in Fall 2022 and
              Spring 2023!

Laura was Contests Director during the 2023-2024 school year!

Raina is a current MIT student in the Class of 2028 who attended Lakeside School in
              Seattle, Washington. She attended MOP in 2022 and has participated
              in math contests since elementary school. Outside of math, she
              enjoys reading, drawing, and playing card games.

Debayu is a current IIT Kanpur student in the Class of 2029
              from India who has been participating in
              math contests for 4 years now and has made it to the National MO
              of his country twice. He qualified in the Sharygin Correspondence
              Round and participated in the Sharygin finals this year (2023).
              His favorite math subject is number theory but he absolutely
              adores combinatorics as well. Other than math, he also likes
              physics, astronomy, quizzing and listening to Post Malone.

Elsa is from the UK. She is an EGMO bronze medalist and she loves
              to row and listen to music. She's super excited to TA for
              Athemath!

Pranav (Pranav1056) is a sophomore at Oxford from India.
              He has been participating in math contests for 2 years and
              cleared INMO in 2022. He has also cleared various stages of IFOMG
              and now represents India at FSJM. Apart from math, he likes to
              play chess, cards, read physics, go out with friends and talk with
              new people.

Gunjan is from India. She has enjoyed Olympiad mathematics ever
              since she was nine, and has participated in numerous contests over
              the past few years. She is a 2 time European Math Girl's Olympiad
              participant and won a bronze medal in 2022, she has attended IMOTC
              thrice. She is also the director of MOTP. When she is not doing
              math she likes to sketch, bake and spend hours on her phone.

Jessica is a current MIT student in the Class of 2028 from Parkland, Florida. Since
              starting math competitions in elementary school, she has attended
              MOP in 2020 and 2021 and was a gold medalist at EGMO 2021.
              Problems involving functional equations are her favorite. Outside
              of math, she enjoys drawing, watching anime, and running.

Annabel is a current MIT student in the Class of 2028 from Seattle. She's enjoyed math
              since elementary school and has attended MOP twice. Outside of
              math, she likes drawing, listening to music, and rowing.

Anurag is from New Delhi, India. His interests are reading,
              working out, combinatorics, number theory and geometry (he is an
              algebra anti-main except poly ofc which is super good). He is also
              interested in Human Psychology and Neurology.

Alex is a current MIT student in the Class of 2028 who attended Lakeside School in Seattle,
              Washington. Alex is a two-time USAJMO winner, USAMO silver, and
              three-time MOP participant, and also attended USA-Canada Mathcamp
              in 2021 and for the first time in-person in 2022. On the list of
              things Alex enjoys doing but is terrible at are soccer, his
              favorite subject rigid combo, and playing the piano. Alex is a
              hardcore science fiction fan (Dune, Foundation, recently Le Guin),
              and plays too many video games.

Emily is a current Harvard student in the Class of 2028 from Toronto, Canada. She earned an
              honourable mention on the Canadian Mathematical Olympiad and a
              perfect score on the Pan-American Girls’ Mathematical Olympiad.
              She enjoys reading, playing games with her friends, and watching
              musicals.

Emily taught *j'AIME the AMC: Algebra Meets Combinatorics* in
              Fall 2023 and Spring 2024!

Kristine is a current MIT student in the Class of 2028. She attended MOP in 2023 and has
              participated in math contests from a young age. She hopes to
              encourage and support other girls on their journeys in math. In
              her free time, she enjoys reading, rock climbing, and all things
              music!

Kristine taught *Combinections* in Fall 2023 and Spring 2024!

Rey Li is a current MIT student in the Class of 2026 who was a USAJMO winner in 2020 and
              attended MOP in 2020 and 2021. Rey loves math and helping others
              with math, and hopes to share the best parts of it with others.
              Outside of math, Rey plays copious amounts of Slay the Spire and
              reads a little too much manga.

Janabel Xia is an MIT graduate who majored in mathematics. In high
              school, she served as her school's math team captain, and was also
              a two-time MOP attendee and an EGMO individual silver medalist on
              team USA. She has seen first-hand and second-hand the experiences
              that discourage young girls to continue pursuing math, and hopes
              to provide support for these girls through Athemath. Outside of
              math, she also enjoys dancing / choreographing, studying music,
              and reading.

Nicole is a current MIT student in the Class of 2027. She has competed in various math
              competitions throughout middle and high school and attended MOP in
              2021. Nicole hopes to encourage girls and nonbinary students to
              participate in whatever excites them, whether it be math, other
              STEM paths, or anything else! Outside of math, she enjoys learning
              languages, listening to music, and hanging out with friends.

Nicole taught *Algebra and Combinatorics Trail Mix* in Fall
              2021, Spring 2022, Fall 2022, and Spring 2023!

Serena Xu is a current MIT student in the Class of 2027. She was a 2021 MOPper and once
              got a perfect score in AMC12. She established GmathIRL and wrote
              Rabbit's Geometry to encourage more participation in STEM fields,
              especially underrepresented genders. She was also an alum of
              Athemath’s first session. Moreover, she is really obsessed with
              EDM and sometimes even remixes different pieces (also 10% DJ) or
              cuts short videos for fun.

Serena taught *Spicy Geo* in Spring 2022, Fall 2022, and
              Spring 2023!

Cordelia is a current MIT student in the Class of 2027. She was a winner for the USAJMO
              2022 and a MOP participant, and she began doing math competitions
              since elementary school. As a transgender woman, she sees
              firsthand many of the struggles women and other gender minorities
              face in STEM fields, and hopes to do a small part in helping to
              alleviate some of their struggles. Aside from math, she enjoys
              playing piano, listening to EDM, and swimming.

Cordelia taught *NT Olympiad Fundamentals* in Fall 2022 and
              Spring 2023!

Holden Mui is an MIT graduate. He taught at a local gifted academy
              and also ran a local math circle. He attended MOP three times, was
              a USAMO Honorable Mention, and placed in the top 25 in the Putnam.
              In addition to math, he also enjoys playing chamber music with
              friends and writing music. He thinks he is the reincarnation of
              Ravel but other people think he is just a turtle.

Isabella Quan is a current MIT student in the Class of 2026. She has competed in math
              contests since 4th grade and attended MOP in 2020 and RSI in 2021.
              When competing in team contests, she was often the only girl among
              several boys, and hopes to encourage and inspire girls who are
              starting off in math. When not working, she enjoys playing
              Pokemon, writing, and listening to music, especially K-pop.

Isabella taught *My Favorite Things* in Spring 2021, Fall
              2021, Spring 2022, and Fall 2022!

Sanjana is a current MIT student in the Class of 2026. She attended MOP in 2019 and 2020, and
              was an EGMO gold medalist in 2020 and 2021. Outside of math, she
              enjoys reading, crosswords, and puzzles.

Sanjana taught *Counting and Probability Principles* in
              Spring 2021 and Spring 2022!

Pravalika is a current MIT student in the Class of 2026. She won a gold medal at the Math
              Prize for Girls Olympiad in 2019 and attended MOP in 2020 and
              2021. Pravalika is also a central leader of the math nonprofit
              inteGIRLS and a regular volunteer at Academy of Hope Adult Public
              Charter School, and she is highly passionate about mathematics,
              education, and activism. She hopes to encourage people of all
              backgrounds to pursue their STEM passions without fear! Outside of
              math, she enjoys reading sci-fi/fantasy (current read:
              *The Weight of the Stars* - K. Ancrum), painting, and
              listening to Rainbow Kitten Surprise.

Pravalika taught *Spicy Counting* in Spring 2021 and Spring
              2022!

Kaylee Ji is a current MIT student in the Class of 2026. Kaylee is a two-time USAJMO
              honorable mention and MOP participant. She was on the Canada
              European Girls' Math Olympiad Team and won a gold medal. Kaylee
              has seen girls discouraged from preparing for harder competitions
              and wishes to assist other girls in their math goals. In her free
              time, she enjoys reading, drawing, and taking walks outside.

Kaylee taught *Algebra in AIME* in Spring 2022!

Andrew Wu is a Yale University graduate, living in the DC
              metropolitan area. He worked as the head problem editor for the
              Yale-run competitions MMATHS and Girls in Math. In high school he
              qualified for USA(J)MO thrice, and published two papers in
              Euclidean geometry. Outside of math, Andrew loves playing piano —
              classical, pop, musical theatre, anything — and he’s passionate
              about educational equity, good writing, and graphic design.

Ilaria Seidel is a current Harvard student in the Class of 2026. She is a second-year
              research student at the MIT PRIMES program, and attended
              USA/Canada Mathcamp in 2019. In her free time, she enjoys playing
              the flute, painting octopuses, and learning languages.

Janette is an MIT graduate who studied Electrical Engineering and
              Computer Science. In middle and high school, she participated in
              various math competitions, including MathCounts, the AMC series,
              and other local and national competitions. She especially loves
              geometry and enjoys sharing her passion in math with younger
              students. Outside of math, Janette is interested in the
              linguistics field of study and spends her free time watching kpop
              and dramas.
